definition: see 壓根兒|压根儿[ya4 gen1 r5]
to press/to push down/to keep under (control)/pressure
strong/powerful/better/slightly more than/vigorous/violent/best in their category, e.g. see 百強|百强[bai3 qiang2]
to force/to compel/to strive/to make an effort
to pass/to spend (time)/measure/limit/extent/degree of intensity/degree (angles, temperature etc)/kilowatt-hour/classifier for events and occurrences

sentences.english: The distribution of earth pressure intensity on the wall slab with depth is non-linear.
sentences.chinese: 土壓力強度沿深度的分佈是非線性的。

sentences.english: The experiential formulas to estimate fluctuating pressure intensity have been given.
sentences.chinese: 提出了估算類似條件下的脈動壓力強度的經驗公式。
